WIKIPEDIA INTEGRATION
This class is concerned with implementing an interface
to communicate with the Wikipedia API.
There is one
attribute
private static String base_URL
, this attribute represents
the base URL, needed to make
queries to the Wikipedia API. This String contains
various URL form attributes, for example to
specify the response in JSON format and so on.
and the
methods
are:
public static String getText(String entity)
, this
method, researches the String given in input
on Wikipedia, by adding it to the base URL attribute.
The HTTP request is done with the
library Jsoup. This process returns a JSON object
from the Wikipedia API; if it contains the
attribute “extract” the method returns it, otherwise
it returns an empty string.
public static int getWikiID (String entity)
, researches
the String given in input on Wikipedia,
by adding it to the base URL attribute. The HTTP request
is done with the library Jsoup. This
process returns a JSON object from the Wikipedia API
from which the matched page ID
(positive integer) is extracted and then returned
by the method. If the String doesn’t match
any page, it returns a control value of -1.
HIGH LEVEL PARSING
This is the central class in our project. It is concerned
with executing the complete pipeline, from
reading the input file, to generating the graph (both
from the analyzed text or from an XML file). The
attributes
are:
private CoreDocument doc
, this attribute represents
the analyzed document through
Stanford Core NLP pipeline. The CoreDocument class
allows access to all the annotations
representing the documents by some built in methods.
private StanfordCoreNLP pipeline
, this attribute represents
the pipeline on which the
document will be annotated.
private Map<String, String> ner
, this attribute is
a HashMap composed by a String key and a
String value. It is used to store the values of the
named entities, found by the Stanford NLP
library, as a name-type pair (e.g. bill gates-person).
